    There seems to be agreement that a sequence of possible completions for a
    partially specified domain name should be tried.  If one of these is to
    treat the name as fully specified, however, then it will cause a request
    to go to a root server, to ask for a top-level domain that probably does
    not exist.

Since the set of root domains should change quite infrequently, would it
make sense for a host to request all the known root domains from a root
server once, and then reject any top-level domain not in that set, without
bothering to ask a root server?
